ue-light/20  bg-white text-blue-vibrant hover:bg-gray-100">Comenzar Prueba Gratuita</button></a></div><div class="bg-white/10 rounded-lg p-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto"><p class="text-lg">En solo 15 minutos, vea cómo más de 150 notificaciones inteligentes pueden optimizar su consultorio y mejorar la participación del paciente en todos los canales.</p></div></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What types of notifications does the Virtual Practice support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Virtual Practice supports automated system notifications and custom notifications. Automated notifications are triggered by events such as appointments, billing, lab results, and care plan reminders. Custom notifications allow clinics to send their own messages. Delivery channels include email, SMS (via your own gateway), mobile push, in-app alerts, and—when WhatsApp Business is integrated—WhatsApp for custom notifications."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I turn off system notifications if my clinic doesn't want them?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Automated notifications are configurable. If your clinic prefers not to send certain types of alerts, you can disable them at the system level."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are notifications secure and HIPAA-compliant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Notifications sent through external channels such as email, SMS, or push never include PII or PHI. Patients receive secure links to log into the portal or mobile app to view sensitive details, supporting HIPAA compliance."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can patients respond to notifications?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Notifications can be interactive. Patients can confirm or cancel appointments with one tap, join telehealth sessions from reminders, and securely access lab results and documents via embedded links. Quick-response buttons can also be configured."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the system support WhatsApp for patient communication?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. WhatsApp can be used when your clinic integrates its WhatsApp Business account. It is available only for custom notifications and not for automated system alerts."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are notifications triggered in the system?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Notifications are workflow-driven and sent automatically when specific events occur, such as appointment bookings and reminders, payment confirmations, lab result availability, new consultation documents, and care plan steps."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can staff still send manual notifications when needed?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Authorized staff can send custom notifications in addition to automated workflows. These can be delivered across multiple channels, including WhatsApp if integrated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do notifications help reduce patient no-shows?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Automated reminders via SMS, push, and in-app alerts help reduce missed appointments. Actionable notifications with confirmation and rescheduling links improve follow-through."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are these notifications different from generic tools like email marketing platforms?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Virtual Practice notifications are built into clinical workflows and are healthcare-specific, compliant by default, and tied to patient actions such as rescheduling or viewing documents. No separate tools or data syncing are required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can notifications reflect my clinic's brand?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Notifications are sent through your clinic's configured email domain, SMS gateway, and optional WhatsApp Business account, ensuring consistent, on-brand communication."}}]}</script><s